C.N. Brown Electricity, LLC TARIFF FERC NO. 1
1. Availability: C.N. Brown Electricity, LLC makes electric energy and capacity available under this Tariff for wholesale sales to purchasers with whom C.N. Brown Electricity, LLC has contracted.
2. Applicability: This Tariff is applicable to all sales of electric energy and/or capacity by C.N. Brown Electricity, LLC.
3. Rates: All sales pursuant to this Tariff shall be made at rates negotiated between the purchaser and C.N. Brown Electricity, LLC.
4. Other Terms and Conditions: All other terms and conditions for purchases of electric energy and capacity shall be established by agreement between the purchaser and C.N. Brown Electricity, LLC.
5. Compliance with Commission Regulations: C.N. Brown Electricity, LLC shall comply with the provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning C.N. Brown Electricity, LLC 's market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes C.N. Brown Electricity, LLC to engage in affiliate sales under this tariff or otherwise restricts or limits C.N. Brown Electricity, LLC's market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning C.N. Brown Electricity, LLC 's market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this Tariff.
6. Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority: C.N. Brown Electricity, LLC has requested and been granted the following waivers and exemptions in connection with its market-based rate authority, pursuant to Commission order approving this Tariff: (i) waiver of Subparts B and C of Part 35 of the Commission's regulations requiring the filing of cost-of-service information, except for sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15 and 35.16; (ii) waiver of Part 41, Part 101, and Part 141 of the Commission's regulations concerning accounting and reporting requirements, except for 18 C.F.R. Section;Section; 141.14 and 141.15; and (iii) blanket authorization under Section 204 of the Federal Power Act, 16 U.S.C. Section; 824c, and Part 34 of the Commission's regulations for all future issuances of securities and assumptions of liability. C.N. Brown Electricity, LLC, Docket No. ER 12-___-000.
7. Seller Category: Seller is a Category 1 seller in all regions, as defined in 18 CFR 35.36(a).
8. This Tariff is effective upon such date as set by the Commission.
